@drinknrun152 It was legal pretty briefly in the Northern Territory of Australia in the 90s too but was overturned in federal government. Legal now in two states in Aus but that's all. I feel Very Passionately about end of life choice for people

Also every time I think of Waitara, that place is tangled with Poppa's death for me. Someone in conversation says they live in Waitara? My brain goes "Waitara, poppa, suicide" in a split second. I see it on a map, a road sign, in the news, whatever. That split second thought.
Also voting yes for the cannabis bill too, fyi

So I care about BOTH things. Palliative care is important, appropriate pain relief is important, respectful care and support is important. Being able to choose to end your life on your terms when you have a terminal illness is also important. People should have the choice

Also because I know palliative care is always brought up with this discussion. I strongly believe that better healthcare services are needed, including palliative care, but not everyone wants palliative care, some people just want to die.

7 years ago my grandfather shot himself in the face on Waitara beach rather than die of cancer.
